<div>
<div align="center"><a href="https://www.directupload.net/" target="_blank" rel="nofollow noopener"><img style="max-width: 100%;" src="https://s15.directupload.net/images/181201/3hladeqx.png" /></a></div>
<br />
<div>
<div align="center"><span style="font-family: 'courier new';">Main informations by : <a title="@shiruyui" href="">Shiruyui</a> , <a style="color: #32e619;" title="@manakhe" href="">ManaKhe</a> , Takarra ,<a style="color: #32e619;" title="@makinayuki" href=""> Makina Yuki</a> , <a style="color: #32e619;" title="@caporal84" href="">caporal84</a></span></div>
<div align="center"><strong>First of all</strong>, let me introduce myself : My IGN is <strong>Mikoto88</strong>, a lvl <strong>364 Enchanter</strong> from start<br />I noticed that enchanters guide from caporal is <strong>Outdated</strong>, so I decided to remaking his guide. I will add updated information such as newest gear and gameplay also with some Walktrough for newbies. Most information that I provide are either proven by myself or by other enchanters. Great credits I give to <a style="color: #32e619;" title="@caporal84" href="/user/11515">caporal84</a> as the original creator of this guide, that really help me in past when I still newb ench QwQ</div>
</div>
<br /><br />
<div>
<div><a style="display: none;">SPOILER: Click to show</a><span style="cursor: pointer;"><span style="font-family: impact; font-size: xx-large;"><strong>Introduction</strong></span></span></div>
<div data-tag="spoiler">Enchanter is unique Wizard branch class. Unlike High wizard or Necromancer, they can use sword and damaging enemies via auto attack. Enchanter is Wizard branch class that capable to dealt high DPS via Autoskill (mostly Magic-Type) and has good tanking or survival ability.<br /><br />Survive as Enchanter is fairly easy because we had Stoneskin which cover your HP with layer that based on your VIT and Illnes Hit which transfer aliment to enemies and make us immune against same aliment for 30 sec.<br /><br />For DPS, Enchanter can become best damager class in Iruna (even beat famous DPS class such as Assassin or High Wizard) if condition meets. Each Enchanter autoskill can reach over 100k damage because we had skill to break autoskill damage limit.<br /><br />However, Enchanter is one of most complicated class in Iruna because you need know what your gear does (since autoskill description rarely described) and how to distribute stats at early level. Moreover, Ench DPS will be limited if we face enemies that hard to be auto attacked.<br /><br /></div>
</div>
<br />
<div><a style="display: none;">SPOILER: Click to show</a><span style="cursor: pointer;"><span style="font-family: impact; font-size: xx-large;"><strong>Requirement</strong></span></span></div>
<div data-tag="spoiler"><span style="font-size: medium;"><strong>Apprenticeship Requirement: </strong></span><br />&bull; <strong>Level 120 Wizard</strong><br />&bull; <strong>Fire Lance 3</strong> (quest in the church at sofya)<br />&bull; <strong>Ice Spear 3</strong> (quest in the churche at sofya)<br />&bull; <strong>Mana Recharge 3</strong> (quest from synthetiser (tbc) at kleya)<br />&bull; <strong>Thunderbolt 1</strong> (quest from Nesri at Saterica)<br /><br /><strong>Then :</strong><br />Talk to Nesri in President's Office, northeast building of Capital city Saterica.<br /><br /><span style="font-size: medium;"><strong>Enchanter Requirement: </strong></span><br /><strong>&bull; Level 140 Apprentice Enchanter</strong><br /><br /><strong>Then :</strong><br />Talk to King Elban in the Palace of Elban City.</div>
<br />
<div><a style="display: none;">SPOILER: Click to show</a><span style="cursor: pointer;"><span style="font-family: impact; font-size: xx-large;"><strong>Pros &amp; Cons</strong></span></span></div>
<div data-tag="spoiler"><span style="font-size: medium;"><strong>Pros:</strong></span><br />-High DPS<br />-Decent Survival even with Full DPS set<br />-Good for Tanking<br />-Almost need no recovery Item for grind or farm<br />-Can Solo &ldquo;almost&rdquo; all Boss<br />-Immune to most of status ailment <br />-Creative gameplay<br /><br /><br /><span style="font-size: medium;"><strong>Cons :</strong></span><br />-Complicated skill and gameplay for new player (for Auto-attack build) <br />-Need correct gear set to do high DPS or Tanking<br />-No AoE<br />-Low Normal attack Damage<br />-Has attack accuracy problem against high evasion enemies</div>
<br />
<div><a style="display: none;">SPOILER: Click to show</a><span style="cursor: pointer;"><span style="font-family: impact;"><strong><span style="font-size: xx-large;">Stats</span></strong></span></span></div>
<div data-tag="spoiler"><strong><span style="font-size: medium;">INT</span></strong>(First priority after AGI 256):<br /> &bull; For MATK (since most ench damage source is magic autoskill)<br /> &bull; For MDEF<br /> &bull; For MP pool<br /> &bull; For ATK with magic swords, magic bows, and throw<br /> &bull; For CGB ATK &amp; MATK boost<br /><br /><span style="font-size: medium;"><strong>VIT</strong></span> (2nd priority if you dont satisfied with your HP pool):<br /> &bull; For more HP and survivability<br /> &bull; For Struggler Hidden (at least 175)<br /> &bull; For DEF<br /><br /><span style="font-size: medium;"><strong>AGI</strong></span> (First priority until 256): <br /> &bull; For EVA and survival (for auto - attack builds, minimum MUST 256)<br /> &bull; For ASPD<br /> &bull; For Hiereus stats bonus<br /><br /><span style="font-size: medium;"><strong>DEX</strong></span>(Last Priority):<br /> &bull; For 0 sec cast time of Magic Blade<br /> &bull; For Hit rate (minimum 70 at low level) <br /> &bull; For ATK and MATK (including via CGB)<br /> &bull; For shorter Cast Time and Skill Delay<br /><br /><span style="font-size: large;"><strong>CRT</strong></span> (not reccomended to add unless you know what you do) :<br /> &bull; For critical hit rate and Critical damage (CRT ench user), so higher normal attack damage and heal from HP heal by attack gear (ex: Eraser, HCB, SSF)<br /> &bull; For higher Magic Blade physical part damage via Hide Attack (only at first hit)<br /><br /><strong><span style="font-size: large;">GL</span></strong>(after AGI 256, DEX 235, VIT min 175, and INT already capped): <br /> &bull; for matk<br /> &bull; for evasion, absolute evasion, and magic evasion<br /> &bull; for magic pierce<br /><br /><span style="font-size: large;"><strong>BL </strong></span><span style="font-size: small;">(if any spare point and only add if GL already maxed)</span>: <br /> &bull; for matk<br /> &bull; for magic pierce<br /> &bull; for more MP</div>
<br />
<div><a style="display: none;">SPOILER: Click to show</a><span style="cursor: pointer;"><span style="font-family: impact; font-size: xx-large;"><strong>Build</strong></span></span></div>
<div data-tag="spoiler">First, unlike past, auto attack on/off function has been implementated which means Magic Blade user can also had AGI for more survival or Auto attack ench can spam Magic Blade without worry about ASPD. Still, there are 2 major build for enchanter:<br /><br />◎<span style="font-size: x-large;"><strong><span style="font-size: large;">Auto Attack Build</span></strong></span>◎<br />Auto attack build mainly focused to dealing high damage via autoskill from gear or skill that proc via normal attack. Unlike most auto attack class, enchanter normal attack damage is the lowest one compared to monk or even samurai. HOWEVER, enchanter potential DPS is highest among all other auto attack class because we can remove Magic Autoskill damage limit, so thats common to see enchanter can do 100k-600k damage in single autoskill. Which means, if we total all 5 auto at once, enchanter can reach 1m+ damage per single attack with attack interval cut feature :3 Here some Auto attack enchanter stats build:<br /><br />▶ ▷ <span style="font-size: large;"><strong>INT DEX focused build :</strong></span> INT, DEX, AGI &amp; VIT (min 256), GL, GB<br /><strong>Weapon Choice:</strong> Magic Sword, Magic Bow (cant draw Hiereus full potential), Throw, Rod, Normal weapon with magic attack chance (ex: Pramia)<br /><strong>Pros : </strong> - Highest Autoskill damage<br /> - Can use almost all enchanter gear set<br /> - High boost from CGB<br /><strong>Cons :</strong> - Low normal attack damage<br /> - Lower survival compared to VIT or AGI focused (by little margin)<br /> - Without tech abi, most attack will miss against high evasion mob/boss <br /><br />▶ ▷ <span style="font-size: large;"><strong>AGI focused build</strong></span> : INT, AGI (300+), DEX, VIT, GL<br /><strong>Weapon Choice:</strong> Hiereus, Magic Bow, Magic Sword, Throw, Rod, Normal weapon with magic attack chance (ex: Pramia)<br /><strong>Pros : </strong> - Highest Evasion among all other build<br /> - Can draw Hiereus full potential<br /> - Many gear selection (including claw)<br /><strong>Cons : </strong> - Lower MATK compared to INT DEX focused Build<br /> - Sometimes, evasion isnt realible<br /> - Without tech abi, most attack will miss against high evasion mob/boss<br /><br />▶ ▷ <strong><span style="font-size: large;">VIT focused build</span></strong> : INT, VIT (300+), DEX, AGI (min 256), GL. <br /><strong>Weapon Choice:</strong> Magic Sword, Magic Bow (cant use Hiereus full potential), Throw, Rod, Normal weapon with magic attack chance (ex: Pramia)<br /><strong>Pros : </strong> - High maxHP and thicker Stoneskin<br /> - Great to counter HP drain/ special attack gimmick<br /> - Highest tanking capability compared to other build<br /><strong>Cons : </strong> - Lower MATK compared to INT DEX focused Build<br /> - Higher damage from rate HP/Special attack<br /> - Without tech abi, most attack will miss against high evasion mob/boss<br /><br />▶ ▷<strong><span style="font-size: large;"> Minimum AGI build</span></strong> : INT, VIT, DEX, AGI (45-150), BL, GL/RL<br /><strong>Weapon Choice:</strong> Magic Sword, Magic Bow, Throw, Rod<br /><strong>Pros : </strong> - More stats to spread<br /> - Easy to build at early level<br /> - Can become magic blade spammer or counter ench<br /><strong>Cons : </strong> - Lowest survival, especially against recent boss<br /> - Need recast stoneskin almost everytime<br /> - Cant use full DPS set against recent boss<br /><br />▶ ▷<span style="font-size: large;"><strong> CRT build</strong></span> : INT, CRT, DEX, VIT &amp; AGI (min 256) <br /><strong>Weapon Choice:</strong> Magic Sword, Magic Bow, Throw, Rod, Claw with magic attack chance (ex: Pramia). All mixed with CRT or ATK stats<br /><strong>Pros :</strong> - Higher hit rate<br /> - Higher heal from HP drain gear such as as Huge Cherry Blossom<br /> - High Magic blade damage on 1st hit (see Magic Blade CRT build)<br /><strong>Cons : </strong> - Lowest DPS compared to other build<br /> - Questionable survival<br /> - Lower magic blade damage after 1st hit<br /><br />.<br />◎<span style="font-size: large;"><strong>Magic Blade Build</strong></span>◎<br />Magic Blade is enchanter skill that can be unlocked at Level 220. This skill main feature are;<br /><br />&ndash;Can make your opponent Dizzy (your enemies takes +10% damage) <br />&ndash;Has two damage part, Physical (ATK based) and Magic (MATK based).<br /><br />Magic Blade spam DPS isnt as high as Auto attack one, but has simple gameplay and still able dealt reasonable damage to newest boss (100k-500k each). Please note that Magic Blade cant critical, spellbursted, or shell break. However, if you has Hide Attack skill, your physical part damage can dealt higher damage based on your Critical Damage part (either from gear, apos, relic, or CRT stats). Here some Magic Blade enchanter stats build:<br /><br />▶ ▷ <span style="font-size: large;"><strong>Tank build </strong></span>: INT, DEX, VIT, GL, BL<br /><strong>Weapon Choice:</strong> Magic Sword, Throw, Special Sword<br /><strong>Pros : </strong> - High MagicDamage part damage<br /> - Consistent DPS<br /> - High tanking ability (Comparable with Knight branch Class)<br /><strong>Cons : </strong> - Low evasion can be troublesome against some boss<br /> - Lower damage compared to Auto attack build<br /> - Rate HP cut damage can be troublesome sometimes<br /><br />▶ ▷<strong><span style="font-size: large;">Counter buil</span><span style="font-size: large;">d</span></strong> : INT, VIT, DEX, BL, GL (Blue dominated cyan Apos) <br /><strong>Weapon Choice:</strong> Rod, Throw<br /><strong>Pros : </strong> - High Magic autoskill counter damage<br /> - Damage disable set can negate damage and heals you with same amount<br /> - Can afk grind at aggressive mob :v<br /><strong>Cons : </strong> - Low evasion can be troublesome against some boss<br /> - Low DPS against boss with slow ASPD<br /> - Weak against Special attack gimmick<br /><br />▶ ▷<span style="font-size: large;"><strong> STR build</strong></span> : INT, STR, DEX (235), VIT (120-175), GL, BL<br /><strong>Weapon Choice:</strong> Throw, Rod, Magic Sword<br /><strong>Pros : </strong> - Highest Magic Blade dps potential<br /> - Has many gear selection (including Normal weapon)<br /> - Consistent DPS <br /><strong>Cons :</strong> - Low survival<br /> - Lower damage compared to Auto attack build<br /> - Lower MP heal compared to other build<br /><br />▶ ▷ <span style="font-size: large;"><strong>CRT Build (One shoot build)</strong></span> : INT, CRT, STR, DEX (235), VIT (120-175) <br /><strong>Weapon Choice:</strong> Throw, Rod, Magic Sword<br /><strong>Pros : </strong> - Highest Magic Blade damage potential on first hit<br /> - Has many gear selection (including Normal weapon)<br /> - Can one shoot many high exp mob and some Episode 3 or lower boss<br /><strong>Cons : </strong> - Low survival<br /> - Only high damage on first hit<br /> - Need Hide attack</div>
