<div><a style="display: none;">SPOILER: Click to show</a><span style="cursor: pointer;"><span style="font-family: impact; font-size: xx-large;"><strong>Building Enchanter Gear Set</strong></span></span></div>
<div data-tag="spoiler"><span style="font-family: impact; font-size: x-large;"><strong>Auto-attack Damage Set</strong></span><br />This set is must for Auto-attack enchanter and you must get this set first before thinking to another set. This set main purpose is to kill enemies as soon as possible either for grind or farming. For damage set, all your gear (including xtall on gear) must have 1 Magic attack chance stats. But there are exception if you dont use Special Status buff, you can use one attack interval cut autoskill on gear and other gear are Magic attack chance.<br />________________________________________________________________________________________________________<br />
<div align="center"><span style="font-size: large;"><strong>Stats Priority:</strong></span><br /> 1) <strong>Magic Attack Chance:</strong><br /> If you want put gear that has no Magic attack Chance stats, make sure that you put xtall with Magic attack chance on it. For damage set, all your gear must have this stats.<br /> 2) <strong>Autoskill Rate:</strong><br />Autoskill rate will be important since you need proc as many as possible autoskill to do consistent DPS. Make sure that you has minimum 30% to 50% autoskill rate (depend on what gear you use) from gear and Draw skill to do consistent damage. <br /> 3) <strong>MATK:</strong><br /> After you had enough autoskill rate, MATK is your priority now. Without good MATK, enchanter dps will be very low. Gear with MATK and&nbsp;autoskill rate will be main priority. But there are exception for Struggler which is best Armor for DPS set after Lv.260.<br /> 4) <strong>Element Magic:</strong><br /> There are a point where high MATK cant even enough to lift your DPS any further. To break this wall, you need Element Magic boost from gear. Make sure you had at least 8k MATK (with spellboost) before thinking to increase this part.<br /> 5) <strong>Others:</strong><br /> Rest up to you. If you want spam Dual Blow, use gear with &ndash;sd. If you want more Spellburst rate, use gear with Spellburst rate boost. But always get points 1-4 on top of priority first.</div>
________________________________________________________________________________________________________<br />
<div align="left">There are some gear set example and short review about that set. For gear review, you can see in my other post. You can two 2 part equip on gear set with another element. For example, you can use 2 dajarte on armor &amp; special equip on your Wind Set.</div>
<div align="left"><span style="font-size: medium;"><strong>Dark Set</strong></span><br /><span style="font-size: small;">Highest damage dealing set in EN Iruna. Can do very high damage but has low proc rate and survival.<br /><strong>Gear Set:</strong><br /><strong>Weapon:</strong> Gram-Frederico; Dark Book Vol.4-Dajarte; Hiereus II- Dajarte<br /><strong>Armor:</strong> Struggler Up-Dajarte; Bellow of Order-Dajarte<br /><strong>Additional:</strong> Fallen Angel Wing-Dunkelis II; Doggy Ears Reup-Dajarte<br /><strong>Special: </strong>Craft Guide Book-Dajarte; Special Blessed Stone-Dajarte &ndash;Agirajarma</span></div>
<br /><span style="font-family: impact; font-size: x-large;"><strong>MP cost Set</strong></span><br />This set is second priority if you want fast farm as enchanter. This set main idea are for as low as possible MP Cost to buffing yourself. You will need this set to fast farm because Limit Break &amp; Qadal eats many MP and has long Skill Delay. Due to Auto Attack ON/OFF function already implemented, you can use it to prevent your char do Auto Attack while you spamming Qadal, buffing yourself, or casting Limit Break.<br />________________________________________________________________________________________________________<br />
<div align="center"><span style="font-size: large;"><strong>Stats Priority:</strong></span><br /> 1) <strong>MP Cost:</strong><br /> Limit Break consume 60% your MaxMP, so you will need this stats to reduce MP Cost as well as other buffing skill. If you want low MP Cost even with Spellboost buff, have at least -130%-200% MP Cost from gear. <br /> 2) <strong>Skill Delay:</strong><br /> Some enchanter skill has long Skill Delay. Magic Barrier has 2 sec, Enchant Weapon ~1.5 sec, Qadal 2 sec, and Limit Break ~4 sec.&nbsp;This SD will affect your killing time, so you need at least -3 sec skill delay to counter them. <br /> 3) <strong>Defensive Stats:</strong><br /> Any Resist + or Evasion + will help you to counter enemies attack while you cast Limit Break or buffing.<br />
<div align="left">________________________________________________________________________________________________________</div>
<div align="left">Here For gear set example:</div>
</div>
<div align="left"><span style="font-size: medium;"><strong>MP Cost Set</strong></span><br /><strong>Gear Set:</strong> Weapon: Moonlight-Rossam; Saint Scripture-Rossam; Amber Sail IV- Kagan<br /><strong>Armor:</strong> Deceiver Up-Rossam; Country Road-Rossam<br /><strong>Additional:</strong> Kijimu Hat-Rossam; Ardour Cachnez-Rossam<br /><strong>Special:</strong> Spec Slot-Rossam; Specia Blessed Stone-Rossam &ndash;Rossam</div>
<br /><span style="font-family: impact; font-size: x-large;"><strong>Damage Negate Set</strong></span><br />There are unique gear that give damage negate feature and some of them give heal hp based on damage you take. On enchanter case, you can make this gear set has &gt;80% proc rate which hard to achive via another class in Iruna. Furthermore, with enchanter Absorb skill, you can also get MP heal via defense. Sounds OP is it? However, this feature hard to achive in practice. Some boss has special attack which cant be negated via this gear. Rate HP attack and over current HP damage cannot be negated via this set. SR gear will help this problem (except on special attack damage). You can mix this gear on DPS set (just put Dragon Mail on armor) for better kill time.<br />________________________________________________________________________________________________________<br />
<div align="center"><span style="font-size: large;"><strong>Stats Priority:</strong></span><br />1) <strong>Damage Disable Autoskill:</strong> Added soon.<br />2) <strong>Autoskill Rate:</strong> Added soon. <br />3) <strong>MaxHP:</strong> Added Soon.<br />4) <strong>Resist &amp; Rate Cut:</strong> Added Soon.<br />________________________________________________________________________________________________________</div>
Example:<strong><br /><span style="font-size: medium;">Damage Negate Set</span></strong><br />Put any xtall except that consume autoskill.<br /><strong>Gear Set:</strong> Weapon: Genius-Frederico; Judgement III-Dajarte<br /><strong>Armor:</strong> Dragon Mail reup-Bodyguard Cordal; Schwremer reup- Bodyguard Cordal<br /><strong>Additional:</strong> Luna Epaullette-Rudolf; Blue Epaullette-Rudolf<br /><strong>Special:</strong> Currently no Damage Negate autoskill on spec</div>
